Chapter 41 - Raw hides and skins 
(other than furskins) and leather
5555
5556
41.01
Raw hides and skins of bovine 
(including buffalo) or equine animals 
(fresh, or salted, dried, limed, pickled 
or otherwise preserved, but not 
tanned, parchment‑dressed or further 
prepared), whether or not dehaired or 
split.

weight per skin not exceeding 8 kg when 
simply dried, 10 kg when dry‑salted, or 
16 kg when fresh, wet‑salted or 
otherwise preserved:
